## Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a flutter project
2. Use the same name
3. The _ in the name is missing but  will reflect in the package

comment_data.body:
Can you give an example with specific names that demonstrate the problem you're seeing?

FYI @stevemessick @helin24

App name: fluter_app
com.rooster-tech.fluterapp <- _ missed and - is allowed
After finish - is removed and _ is showing again

@SmartManoj thanks for the report, can you clarify the steps you're following to create your app?

My guess was the following, but I cannot replicate your issue this way:
1. Go to File -> New -> Project
2. Select flutter SDK path
3. Enter for "Project name" a name that has an underscore, e.g. `underscore_test`
4. Click "Finish"
(when I try this, I see underscore_test in the project menu and in the generated README.md)

Can you also describe/screenshot where you've been seeing this value within IntelliJ? `com.rooster-tech.fluterapp`

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
This appears to have been fixed. If you still have this problem we can re-open it.

title: In package name _ is missing and - is allowed when entering package name for flutter
